Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Boil the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams}, ~{12-13%minutes}. Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and @Sliced Mushrooms{80%grams}, ~{6-8%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, open the remaining sachets.

Stir in the @Gochujang Paste{50%grams}, @Ketjap Manis{25%grams}, @Peanut Butter{30%grams}, @Soy Sauce{15%milliliter} and @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliter}. Add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams}. Bring to the boil. Simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}. Top with the beef stir-fry. Enjoy!